Place drumsticks in a 13-in. x 9-in. x 2-in. baking dish. Arrange onion over drumsticks. Pour tomatoes on top. Combine the water, bouillon, garlic, salt, oregano and basil; pour over onion. Sprinkle with parsley. Cover and bake at 325 degrees F for 2 hours or until tender and a meat thermometer reads 180 degrees F.